  <Summary>The Curse of Morby Castle: Lance Cauldan plans to scare his new wife to death, but his aide-de-camp has her own plans.

Divide and Murder: John isn't worried about being exposed for taking kickbacks because he can separate his spirit from his body and murder his accuser.  But he doesn't count on his victim entering his body and filing a full confession the next time he vacates his form.

The Tomb of Ramfis: Adam and Gertrude find a flower, then a wall falls and crushes them.

Dead Man's Diary: Conrad Crane enters J. B. Dales' employ as food-taster, but Crane intends that Dales die not from poisoning, but from starvation, as Crane's father did.

Domain of the Damned!: Dan Walker washes ashore on a tropical island filled with people he thinks look like freaks.  He successfully escapes, but not without a significant change to his own appearance.

</Summary>
